cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of delay-throughput tradeoff in wireless networks, which is a common topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper specifically focuses on wireless networks and their performance, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the power allocation strategy and buffer management, which are related to system and control theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions packet arrival processes, which can be related to multimedia traffic in wireless networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a new notion of performance called effective throughput, which can be seen as a data structure for measuring network performance.
